# Adding Images

----
## - use your terminal to docker commands { CMD, Linux Terminal or Whatever You Use }

--> docker pull imagename { it will work when the image Exist }
    Example - docker pull archlinux
    
## Starting Tutorial Already Taught How to Create a Image { but how create a resources and other stuff will Learn Later }

--> docker run -t -d --name name1 name2   <-- this one is yours { after pulling the image above step }
--> docker exec -it name1 shell_name (sh or bash)

--> docker ps { list all running images }
### tags -> tags give us the ability to download different version of the image { source networkchuck }

--> " : " is used to specify the tag, we can give our tags while building an image

TO STOP THE IMAGE:
-> docker stop name1
-> docker start name1
-> docker stats  { view resources being used }
